PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772831515
OL,3,CWho are the Kurds, and could they
OL,4,Ctopple the Iranian regime?
OL,6,FAfter Iran's 1979 Islamic Revolution,
OL,7,Fthe new theocracy also battled Kurdish
OL,8,Finsurgents. Iranian forces destroyed
OL,9,FKurdish towns and villages in fighting
OL,10,Fthat killed thousands over several
OL,11,Fmonths.
OL,13,FWhile they share a desire to see the
OL,14,Fcurrent authorities ousted, the
OL,15,FKurdish groups have also butted heads
OL,16,Fwith other opposition groups ` notably
OL,17,Fthe faction led by the former shah's
OL,18,Fson, Reza Pahlavi, who has accused the
OL,19,FKurds of being separatists aiming to
OL,20,Fcarve up Iran.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
