OL,3,CWho are the Kurds, and could they
OL,4,Ctopple the Iranian regime?
OL,6,FMany Kurds feel they have been used in
OL,7,Fthe past by the United States and then
OL,8,Fabandoned.
OL,10,FThe Kurds were critical during the
OL,11,Ffight against ISIS, only to find the
OL,12,FUS walked away from the support they
OL,13,Fhad expected once that war was won.
OL,15,FThe presence of armed Iranian Kurdish
OL,16,Fgroups in northern Iraq has also been
OL,17,Fa point of friction between the
OL,18,Fcentral Iraqi government in Baghdad
OL,19,Fand Tehran.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31716
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772831515
OL,3,CWho are the Kurds, and could they
OL,4,Ctopple the Iranian regime?
OL,6,FIraq in 2023 reached an agreement with
OL,7,FIran to disarm the groups and move
OL,8,Fthem from their bases near the border
OL,9,Fareas with Iran ` where they
OL,10,Fpotentially posed an armed challenge
OL,11,Fto Tehran ` into camps designated by
OL,12,FBaghdad.
OL,14,FTheir military bases were shut down
OL,15,Fand their movement within Iraq
OL,16,Frestricted, but the groups did not
OL,17,Fgive up their weapons.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
